properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 21 at 7:27AM CST until January 21 at 4:00PM CST by NWS Aberdeen SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow. Winds gusting as high as 50 mph.

* WHERE...Codington and Deuel Counties.

* WHEN...Until 4 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Blowing snow could significantly reduce visibility.
The hazardous conditions could impact the morning or evening
commute. Gusty winds could bring down tree branches. The cold
wind chills as low as 25 below zero could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
